  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\r\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \r\n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\r\n<!--     https://github.com/PegasysEng/artemis/blob/master/CODE-OF-CONDUCT.md -->\r\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\r\n<!--   * Read the debugging wiki: https://github.com/PegasysEng/artemis/wiki/debugging -->\r\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3APegasysEng/Artemis -->\r\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nIn order to detect the end of an Epoch, I had to write this code:\r\n\r\n```\r\nlong epoch_length = Integer.toUnsignedLong(Constants.EPOCH_LENGTH);\r\nlong zero = Integer.toUnsignedLong(0);\r\nUINT64 slot = state.getSlot();\r\nif( slot.modulo(epoch_length).equals(UInt64.valueOf(zero)) ){\r\n     System.out.println(\"New Epoch\")\r\n      epochProcessor(state);\r\n}\r\n```\r\nThis is just a simple example.  Our Constatnts.java are ints, which need to perform a modulus on UINT64s, and our helper functions in BeaconState.java all expect ints. The state transition logic cannot be completed without a fix here.  \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Would it help to make the constants types that compatible with UINT64 operations?\r\n* add more helper functions to UINT64?\r\n\r\n",
